            </p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Let <m>x</m> and <m>y</m> be distinct integers.
          Prove that for each natural number <m>n</m>,
          <m>\left( x - y \right)</m> divides <m>\left( x^n - y^n \right)</m>.
