      <li xml:id="exer_sec51-cong">
        <p>
          Prove Part<nbsp/><xref ref="T_propsofcong3"/> of <xref ref="T_propsofcong">Theorem</xref>
          from <xref ref="S_cases"></xref>.
          Let <m>n \in \mathbb{N}</m> and let <m>a</m> and <m>b</m> be integers.
          For each <m>m \in \N</m>,
          if <m>a \equiv b \pmod n</m>,
          then <m>a^m \equiv b^m \pmod n</m>.
